-- Rangers Defeat Capitals 3-1 in Game 1 of NHL Playoff Series
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-04-28T21:43:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/rangers-defeat-capitals-3-1-in-game-1-of-nhl-playoff-series.html
The  New York Rangers  beat the
Washington Capitals 3-1 in the opening game of their National
Hockey League second-round playoff series.  Chris Kreider and Brad Richards scored 90 seconds apart in
the third period to give the Rangers, the top seed in the
Eastern Conference, the win. New York’s Artem Anisimov and
Washington’s Jason Chimera had goals in the second period.  New York hosts Game 2 in the best-of-seven series in two
days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  